                            <comment id="17871995" author="llowinge" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 13:12:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is, that camel somehow isn&apos;t able to figure out the basePath of URL based on relative part in openapi.json (&quot;servers&quot;:[&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/api/v3&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;]).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17872002" author="llowinge" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 13:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When i use manually `?host=&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080&lt;/a&gt;` it works. But looks more like workaround than fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17872023" author="zhfeng" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 14:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, do you check it with camel-4.x ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17872025" author="llowinge" created="Thu, 8 Aug 2024 14:31:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zhfeng&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zhfeng&quot;&gt;zhfeng&lt;/a&gt; With Cemel 4.7.0 it fails with different error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
[el-1) thread #1 - timer:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//test] TimerConsumer                  WARN  Error processing exchange. Exchange[5DDB809D0CED7B5-0000000000000000]. Caused by: [org.apache.camel.http.base.HttpOperationFailedException - HTTP operation failed invoking http://localhost:8080/api/v3/api/v3/pet with statusCode: 404]
&lt;/span&gt;org.apache.camel.http.base.HttpOperationFailedException: HTTP operation failed invoking http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//localhost:8080/api/v3/api/v3/pet with statusCode: 404&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17873098" author="zhfeng" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 05:05:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, it does not handle the relative url correctly. Refer to the spec &lt;a href=&quot;https://swagger.io/docs/specification/api-host-and-base-path/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://swagger.io/docs/specification/api-host-and-base-path/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;The URLs in the&#160;servers&#160;array can be relative, such as&#160;/v2. In this case, the URL is resolved against the server that hosts the given OpenAPI definition.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17873235" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 15:23:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe this should be backported to 4.4.x branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17873355" author="zhfeng" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2024 00:07:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, I will do&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17874788" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 06:36:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did you backport this ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17874846" author="zhfeng" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2024 10:43:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, it is backport to 4.4.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
